<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05006f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05006f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05006f"> 6(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP judge of men of Erin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">for forty days and nights <font color="green">[St. Patrick]</font> was alone upon the mountain <font color="green">[Croagh Patrick]</font> wrestling in prayer with God &hellip; No food or drink passed his lips &hellip; Then, says the writer of the <cite>Tripartite</cite>, he claimed from God that on the day that &ldquo;the twelve royal seats shall be on the Mount, and when the four rivers of fire shall be about the Mount, and when the three peoples shall be there &mdash; viz., the people of heaven, the people of earth, and the people of hell &mdash; <mark>I myself shall be the judge over the men of Erin</mark> on that day&rdquo;. <small> William Bullen Morris, <a name="WBML" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WBML"><cite title="source">The Life of Saint Patrick Apostle of Ireland</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1890) 210-11</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
